The Walt Disney company is strengthening its foothold in India's entertainment industry by paying $203m (Â£104m) to increase its stake in UTV, a film and television producer based in Mumbai. Under the deal, which is one of Hollywood's biggest steps into south Asia, Disney's shareholding in UTV will rise from 13.7% to 32.1%.UTV is best known in Europe and America for co-producing last year's hit movie The Namesake which followed the struggles of Gogol Ganguli, the son of Indian immigrants living in New York.